{"word":"H2648 - חָפַז - châphaz - khaw-faz' - Haste","slug":"H2648","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">חָפַז</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>châphaz"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>khaw-faz'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Haste"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D7;&#x05E4;&#x05D6; - cha&#x0302;phaz</b> - <i>khaw-faz'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>start</i> up suddenly, that is, (by implication) to <i>hasten</i> away, to <i>fear: - </i>(make) haste (away), tremble."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2649\">H2649</a>"}]}